title: Public Health and Municipal Services Ordinance (Cemeteries) (Amendment of Fifth Schedule) Order 2012 to be gazetted
content_text:
p>
    The Government will gazette the Public Health and Municipal Services 
    Ordinance (Cemeteries) (Amendment of Fifth Schedule) Order 2012 (the Order) 
    on November 9. The Order deletes the New Kowloon Cemetery No. 2 (Little 
    Sisters of the Poor Cemetery) from Part II (i.e. the list of private 
    cemeteries) of the Fifth Schedule to the Public Health and Municipal 
    Services Ordinance (Cap. 132)(the Fifth Schedule) and deletes the Garden of

Remembrance (GoR) at Cape Collinson from Part I (i.e. the list of public 
    cemeteries) of the same Schedule. The New Kowloon Cemetery No. 2 (Little Sisters of the Poor Cemetery) was 
    designated as a private cemetery in Part II of the Fifth Schedule in 1928. 
    In 2003, the operator of the cemetery handed over the site for the 
    redevelopment of the St. Joseph's Home for the Aged. In February 2006, the

Town Planning Board approved the redevelopment proposal and the approval was 
    further renewed in February 2010. The cemetery site now forms part of a lot 
    in a land exchange proposal currently under negotiation between the lot 
    owner and the Lands Department. The cemetery operator has confirmed that all 
    human remains previously buried in the cemetery in question had already been 
    relocated either to the Cheung Sha Wan Catholic Cemetery or to the Chai Wan 
    Catholic Cemetery. The site is no longer used as a cemetery and should

Catholic Cemetery. The site is no longer used as a cemetery and should 
    therefore be deleted from the Fifth Schedule. GoRs and public cemeteries are at present subject to provisions in two 
    different pieces of subsidiary legislation, namely the Cremation and Gardens 
    of Remembrance Regulation (Cap. 132 sub. leg. M) and the Public Cemeteries 
    Regulation (Cap. 132 sub. leg. BI). The GoR at Cape Collinson is currently

included in both Part I "Public Cemeteries" and Part VII "Gardens of 
    Remembrance" of the Fifth Schedule and the listing is confusing. The 
    Government proposes to remove the duplication by deleting the GoR at Cape 
    Collinson from Part I of the Fifth Schedule. The Order will be tabled in the Legislative Council on November 14. Subject 
    to smooth passage through the negative vetting procedures of the Legislative 
    Council, the Order will commence on January 11, 2013.
